      <hr>
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <p>Description of the complex relationship between the item described in the record and
         other items that cannot be adequately generated from the linking entry fields
                  760-787.
      </p>
      <p>In some cases the field is used to state a relationship when no corresponding linking
                     entry fields are present, such as for the following:      </p>
      <ul>
         <li class="nobullet">a regular-print reprint to provide details of the original publication;</li>
         <li class="nobullet">a serial bearing a relationship to a monograph, or other non-serial publication;</li>
         <li class="nobullet">a serial bearing a relationship to one or more publications which cannot be named;</li>
         <li class="nobullet">a serial issued in more than one frequency when two or more records are
                        required.
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>When used, this field appears in addition to any relevant linking entry fields.</p>
      <hr>
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> INDICATORS
      </h4>
      <ul>
         <li>Both indicators are undefined; each contains a blank (#).</li>
      </ul>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> SUBFIELD CODES
      </h4>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$a - Linking entry complexity note</strong> <div class="description">Catalog entry for the related title and a statement describing the
                           relationship.
         </div>
